-- Kuzbass Fuel 2011 Sales Advance 25% on Russian Coal Exports
-- B y   I l y a   K h r e n n i k o v
-- 2012-02-01T06:00:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-01/kuzbass-fuel-2011-sales-advance-25-on-russian-coal-exports.html
Kuzbass Fuel Co., a Russian coal
producer for power stations, said sales by volume gained 25
percent last year as exports to  Europe  and  Asia  surged.  The company sold 10.66 million metric tons of coal last
year, when it increased output 28 percent to 8.74 million tons,
Kuzbass Fuel said in a statement today. Fourth-quarter output
rose 15 percent from the same period of 2010 to 2.57 million
tons, while sales increased 22 percent to 3.34 million tons.  Some of the coal Kuzbass sold came from third parties.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ilya Khrennikov in Moscow at 
